1
00:00:00,790 --> 00:00:02,700
The food here is actually pretty good.

2
00:00:02,793 --> 00:00:04,243
Yeah, not bad.

3
00:00:07,210 --> 00:00:08,410
Can you pour me some water?

4
00:00:09,000 --> 00:00:11,090
Eating at a place like this,

5
00:00:11,360 --> 00:00:12,770
with zero atmosphere...

6
00:00:12,840 --> 00:00:14,500
It's actually kind of relaxing.

7
00:00:15,900 --> 00:00:16,900
Thanks.

8
00:00:17,160 --> 00:00:18,160
You know...

9
00:00:18,410 --> 00:00:19,410
Right now,

10
00:00:19,530 --> 00:00:22,110
I wish time would just stand still.

11
00:00:23,870 --> 00:00:25,070
If only Fukami

12
00:00:25,110 --> 00:00:26,780
felt the same way,

13
00:00:26,900 --> 00:00:27,900
that would be nice.

14
00:00:28,540 --> 00:00:29,540
Want some?

15
00:00:30,820 --> 00:00:32,890
- I want this one.
- No, not that one.

16
00:00:32,900 --> 00:00:36,200
"Unexpectedly Naughty Fukami"

17
00:00:37,300 --> 00:00:41,300
(Episode 8)

18
00:00:43,730 --> 00:00:46,060
A transfer...?

19
00:00:47,890 --> 00:00:50,190
Actually, the Hokkaido branch reached out.

20
00:00:50,460 --> 00:00:51,789
Sales are down over there,

21
00:00:51,790 --> 00:00:53,910
so they want to send someone talented.

22
00:00:54,940 --> 00:00:57,150
Hokkaido, huh?

23
00:00:57,920 --> 00:00:59,620
Plus, it's a promotion to section chief.

24
00:00:59,650 --> 00:01:01,500
It'll be great for your career.

25
00:01:02,550 --> 00:01:04,000
It's pretty far away, though.

26
00:01:06,470 --> 00:01:07,470
Kaji-kun,

27
00:01:07,710 --> 00:01:10,440
surely there's someone
you'd hate to leave behind.

28
00:01:11,860 --> 00:01:12,860
Ah.

29
00:01:13,310 --> 00:01:14,610
It's not really like that.

30
00:01:15,780 --> 00:01:18,320
I think it's a good chance to settle down.

31
00:01:19,130 --> 00:01:22,409
A lot of people get married when
they transfer. Just look around.

32
00:01:22,410 --> 00:01:25,510
It's hard to find the
right timing otherwise.

33
00:01:33,140 --> 00:01:34,700
At our company,

34
00:01:35,090 --> 00:01:36,890
unless there are special circumstances,

35
00:01:37,300 --> 00:01:38,970
you can't really turn down a transfer.

36
00:01:50,170 --> 00:01:51,170
Kaji-san.

37
00:01:51,560 --> 00:01:53,530
The new product catalogs are here.

38
00:01:53,760 --> 00:01:54,760
Oh.

39
00:01:54,770 --> 00:01:57,360
- These are for the expo. I'll take them.
- Thanks.

40
00:01:57,650 --> 00:01:59,250
- Thanks.
- Thank you.

41
00:01:59,960 --> 00:02:00,960
The most important thing

42
00:02:01,200 --> 00:02:03,000
is what you've built at this company.

43
00:02:03,076 --> 00:02:04,176
If it were me,

44
00:02:04,610 --> 00:02:06,060
I'd never say no.

45
00:02:07,580 --> 00:02:10,060
Who doesn't want a promotion?

46
00:02:13,364 --> 00:02:16,337
[Signs hanging in the back showing
Kaji being the top salesperson]

47
00:02:18,340 --> 00:02:19,440
Lately,

48
00:02:19,450 --> 00:02:22,030
we've been meeting every week we're free.

49
00:02:22,870 --> 00:02:26,300
Today, we're just chilling at
his place making dumplings.

50
00:02:28,570 --> 00:02:29,570
But...

51
00:02:29,750 --> 00:02:31,330
to Fukami,

52
00:02:31,710 --> 00:02:33,890
it doesn't seem like we're actually dating.

53
00:02:35,790 --> 00:02:36,890
To a guy like him,

54
00:02:37,560 --> 00:02:38,830
what does "dating"

55
00:02:39,250 --> 00:02:40,250
even mean?

56
00:02:41,030 --> 00:02:42,030
Ah.

57
00:02:42,480 --> 00:02:43,650
I don't get it,

58
00:02:44,226 --> 00:02:45,796
but I want to try to understand.

59
00:02:48,010 --> 00:02:49,010
But for that to happen,

60
00:02:49,587 --> 00:02:51,107
we need to be close to each other...

61
00:02:53,250 --> 00:02:54,700
Hey, you're terrible at this.

62
00:02:55,700 --> 00:02:57,100
You're putting in too much filling.

63
00:02:57,760 --> 00:02:59,140
It all tastes the same anyway.

64
00:03:00,180 --> 00:03:01,180
What do you mean "the same"?

65
00:03:01,180 --> 00:03:02,180
Huh?

66
00:03:10,770 --> 00:03:11,870
I have to tell him.

67
00:03:12,490 --> 00:03:13,720
About the transfer.

68
00:03:19,340 --> 00:03:20,340
If I go,

69
00:03:20,880 --> 00:03:22,990
what's going to happen to us?

70
00:03:25,720 --> 00:03:27,080
It's not like we're dating.

71
00:03:27,830 --> 00:03:28,830
And it's not like

72
00:03:28,855 --> 00:03:31,155
we've made any promises about the future.

73
00:03:35,950 --> 00:03:38,070
Doing it in the kitchen is a bit...

74
00:03:38,620 --> 00:03:39,760
That's not what I meant!

75
00:04:14,570 --> 00:04:15,570
It's out.

76
00:04:16,190 --> 00:04:17,190
Yeah.

77
00:04:24,520 --> 00:04:25,800
I don't want to let go.

78
00:04:27,600 --> 00:04:28,700
I can't let go.

79
00:04:33,570 --> 00:04:34,570
Sorry.

80
00:04:34,980 --> 00:04:36,080
Are you okay?

81
00:04:38,940 --> 00:04:40,040
What's wrong?

82
00:04:40,670 --> 00:04:42,790
You're being really clingy today...

83
00:04:48,590 --> 00:04:49,590
Hey.

84
00:04:50,030 --> 00:04:51,030
Can we go again?

85
00:04:56,600 --> 00:05:00,050
We're all out of condoms.

86
00:05:02,490 --> 00:05:04,030
Then never mind.

87
00:05:13,070 --> 00:05:14,070
It's fine.

88
00:05:18,050 --> 00:05:19,440
I've never tried it before,

89
00:05:20,830 --> 00:05:21,930
but let's give it a shot.

90
00:05:22,630 --> 00:05:23,630
Kaji.

91
00:05:27,260 --> 00:05:28,800
Tell me if it's too much.

92
00:05:37,820 --> 00:05:39,590
This...

93
00:05:39,910 --> 00:05:40,910
So fast.

94
00:05:44,560 --> 00:05:45,660
What should I do?

95
00:05:47,360 --> 00:05:48,460
Like this.

96
00:06:02,150 --> 00:06:03,670
This is like porn.

97
00:06:07,160 --> 00:06:09,980
We have terrible chemistry.

98
00:06:10,710 --> 00:06:11,710
True.

99
00:06:14,710 --> 00:06:18,530
It's warm and feels a bit naughty,

100
00:06:19,470 --> 00:06:22,030
but the pleasure isn't that different.

101
00:06:24,340 --> 00:06:26,230
What are you, a sex sommelier?

102
00:06:27,470 --> 00:06:28,970
You idiot.

103
00:06:33,010 --> 00:06:34,010
Honestly.

104
00:06:34,740 --> 00:06:35,740
You seem fine.

105
00:06:37,330 --> 00:06:39,540
I thought you were feeling sick again.

106
00:06:42,810 --> 00:06:43,810
Um...

107
00:06:44,590 --> 00:06:45,590
Fukami.

108
00:06:52,640 --> 00:06:54,630
My sister's pregnant with her second.

109
00:06:55,720 --> 00:06:57,240
She's due next year.

110
00:07:01,600 --> 00:07:02,600
Sorry.

111
00:07:03,170 --> 00:07:04,970
Did you have something to say?

112
00:07:06,830 --> 00:07:08,680
I forgot what it was.

113
00:07:15,460 --> 00:07:17,290
What would Fukami say?

114
00:07:18,270 --> 00:07:19,370
If I...

115
00:07:19,710 --> 00:07:21,000
wasn't around anymore?

116
00:07:28,340 --> 00:07:30,000
I heard from the manager

117
00:07:30,140 --> 00:07:32,350
that Kaji-san is transferring.

118
00:07:33,540 --> 00:07:34,740
Kaji-san is transferring?

119
00:07:34,960 --> 00:07:36,269
He's so talented.

120
00:07:36,270 --> 00:07:37,850
Why would Sales let him go?

121
00:07:37,980 --> 00:07:40,850
But the manager said it's a promotion.

122
00:07:42,020 --> 00:07:44,290
If it's a promotion,
he can't really say no.

123
00:07:44,820 --> 00:07:46,510
I'll miss him.

124
00:08:01,500 --> 00:08:03,200
(Network connection under repair)

125
00:08:04,210 --> 00:08:05,210
Fukami.

126
00:08:05,290 --> 00:08:06,640
The internet's out.

127
00:08:06,840 --> 00:08:08,100
It's resetting?

128
00:08:10,600 --> 00:08:11,950
It's back up now.

129
00:08:14,110 --> 00:08:15,210
What's wrong?

130
00:08:15,980 --> 00:08:17,210
Are you feeling okay?

131
00:08:18,480 --> 00:08:20,210
Is anyone still here?

132
00:08:20,480 --> 00:08:22,230
It's getting late.

133
00:08:22,690 --> 00:08:24,770
Wait, is no one here?

134
00:08:25,510 --> 00:08:26,510
If we don't finish this,

135
00:08:26,680 --> 00:08:28,140
we won't be able to work.

136
00:08:31,310 --> 00:08:33,840
Hey, we're at the office.

137
00:08:34,470 --> 00:08:35,770
Are you out of your mind?

138
00:08:37,290 --> 00:08:38,650
Maybe.

139
00:08:51,540 --> 00:08:52,540
Wait.

140
00:08:53,300 --> 00:08:54,300
Shower.

141
00:08:55,040 --> 00:08:56,040
No.

142
00:09:00,580 --> 00:09:02,440
You're acting really weird today.

143
00:09:05,370 --> 00:09:06,470
I said wait.

144
00:09:09,060 --> 00:09:11,100
You're transferring
somewhere far away, aren't you?

145
00:09:11,590 --> 00:09:12,590
You...

146
00:09:14,200 --> 00:09:15,200
How?

147
00:09:15,480 --> 00:09:16,940
Where did you hear that?

148
00:09:18,770 --> 00:09:19,380
To you,

149
00:09:19,381 --> 00:09:21,200
I might just be one of many.

150
00:09:21,910 --> 00:09:24,710
But I only do this with you.

151
00:09:24,910 --> 00:09:26,800
Right now, you're the only one for me too.

152
00:09:26,910 --> 00:09:29,460
Then shouldn't you have told me first?

153
00:09:29,870 --> 00:09:31,590
I haven't told anyone.

154
00:09:32,410 --> 00:09:33,510
About the transfer.

155
00:09:33,750 --> 00:09:35,860
I couldn't say anything
until it was official.

156
00:09:36,530 --> 00:09:38,980
I don't want to hear your excuses.

157
00:09:41,000 --> 00:09:42,970
You're the one leaving.

158
00:09:43,320 --> 00:09:44,870
What do you actually want?

159
00:09:45,480 --> 00:09:47,470
Just tell me the truth.

160
00:09:49,730 --> 00:09:52,690
Don't think you can play it cool with me.

161
00:10:11,910 --> 00:10:12,910
I...

162
00:10:14,420 --> 00:10:15,520
don't have the confidence.

163
00:10:21,910 --> 00:10:22,910
With the distance...

164
00:10:23,560 --> 00:10:24,560
and the physical stuff...

165
00:10:25,690 --> 00:10:27,520
If we lose the one thing
keeping us together,

166
00:10:28,760 --> 00:10:30,010
it'll never work.

167
00:10:33,970 --> 00:10:35,080
Someone like me,

168
00:10:35,640 --> 00:10:37,930
who wasn't even loved by his parents...

169
00:10:41,450 --> 00:10:46,890
(To Aki-kun)

170
00:10:56,570 --> 00:10:58,630
Wait, what are you talking about?

171
00:10:59,360 --> 00:11:00,360
Your parents...

172
00:11:00,720 --> 00:11:01,900
That's not true at all.

173
00:11:02,910 --> 00:11:04,730
You wouldn't understand.

174
00:11:09,590 --> 00:11:11,950
Looking at you and your sister,

175
00:11:13,450 --> 00:11:15,000
it's obvious you had a great family.

176
00:11:15,600 --> 00:11:17,680
You were raised with so much love.

177
00:11:19,070 --> 00:11:21,780
Kaji-san, please get
along with my brother.

178
00:11:29,840 --> 00:11:31,430
It's like a constant reminder

179
00:11:31,880 --> 00:11:33,830
that I'm not like you guys.

180
00:11:36,080 --> 00:11:37,080
It hurts.

181
00:11:41,060 --> 00:11:43,040
I'm the one who hurt you.

182
00:11:45,130 --> 00:11:46,130
No.

183
00:11:46,140 --> 00:11:50,410
- That's not it.
- I've been happy.

184
00:11:52,010 --> 00:11:53,910
Doing all those things with you.

185
00:11:55,710 --> 00:11:57,950
But if being with me hurts you...

186
00:12:01,080 --> 00:12:02,080
Fukami.

187
00:12:03,650 --> 00:12:05,560
No, I don't want this.

188
00:12:06,270 --> 00:12:07,780
I don't want to be apart.

189
00:12:08,390 --> 00:12:09,600
Don't leave me.

190
00:12:12,980 --> 00:12:15,080
I've had enough too.

191
00:12:15,610 --> 00:12:18,060
I'm tired of you messing with me.

192
00:12:19,920 --> 00:12:21,330
This is perfect.

193
00:12:22,040 --> 00:12:24,090
You're transferring.

194
00:12:25,790 --> 00:12:27,040
It's been fun,

195
00:12:28,310 --> 00:12:30,500
but I didn't know how to end it.

196
00:12:31,910 --> 00:12:34,460
I'm ready to try someone new anyway.

197
00:12:34,710 --> 00:12:35,710
Are you serious?

198
00:12:37,590 --> 00:12:39,050
With your looks,

199
00:12:39,790 --> 00:12:42,000
you'll find someone else in no time.

200
00:12:51,520 --> 00:12:53,170
Let's end this...

201
00:12:54,140 --> 00:12:55,500
between us.

202
00:13:02,210 --> 00:13:03,726
(Preview)
He's someone important to you, right?

203
00:13:03,750 --> 00:13:05,220
That guy...

204
00:13:05,300 --> 00:13:06,390
isn't happy with me.

205
00:13:06,810 --> 00:13:08,790
Thank you for everything at HQ.

206
00:13:09,090 --> 00:13:11,440
Are you just looking for one last lay?

207
00:13:11,520 --> 00:13:12,313
Idiot.

208
00:13:12,337 --> 00:13:13,940
I'll be waiting for you.

209
00:13:14,330 --> 00:13:15,330
Their final night...

210
00:13:15,710 --> 00:13:16,710
begins now.

